:wetland_ecosystem rdfs:label "wetland ecosystem" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:onProperty :has_part ;
            owl:someValuesFrom [ owl:intersectionOf ( :planetary_landmass [ a owl:Restriction ;
                                owl:onProperty :composed_primarily_of ;
                                owl:someValuesFrom [ owl:intersectionOf ( :soil [ a owl:Restriction ;
                                                    owl:onProperty :has_quality ;
                                                    owl:someValuesFrom :wet ] ) ] ] ) ] ],
        :ecosystem ;
    :has_definition "A terrestrial ecosystem which is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions."^^xsd:string ;
    :has_exact_synonym "WETLAND"^^xsd:string,
        "Wetland"^^xsd:string ;
    :has_narrow_synonym "EstuarineWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "LacustrineWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "MarineWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "PalustrineWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "RiparianWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "TerrestialWetland"^^xsd:string,
        "back marsh"^^xsd:string,
        "backswamp"^^xsd:string,
        "backwater"^^xsd:string,
        "barrier flat"^^xsd:string,
        "blanket bog"^^xsd:string,
        "bog"^^xsd:string,
        "cienaga"^^xsd:string,
        "dismal"^^xsd:string,
        "everglade"^^xsd:string,
        "floating marsh"^^xsd:string,
        "forested wetland"^^xsd:string,
        "marsh"^^xsd:string,
        "mire"^^xsd:string,
        "mud flat"^^xsd:string,
        "peat cutting area"^^xsd:string,
        "peatland"^^xsd:string,
        "quagmire"^^xsd:string,
        "quaking bog"^^xsd:string,
        "riparian area"^^xsd:string,
        "slash"^^xsd:string,
        "slough"^^xsd:string,
        "slue"^^xsd:string,
        "swamp forest"^^xsd:string,
        "tulelands"^^xsd:string ;
    :has_related_synonym "moor"^^xsd:string,
        "morass"^^xsd:string,
        "muskeg"^^xsd:string .

:composed_primarily_of rdfs:label "composed primarily of" .

:ecosystem rdfs:label "ecosystem" .

:has_part rdfs:label "has part" .

:has_quality rdfs:label "has quality" .

:planetary_landmass rdfs:label "planetary landmass" .

:soil rdfs:label "soil" .

:wet rdfs:label "wet" .

,"The wetland ecosystem is a sub-class of ecosystem and it is partially composed of an intersection of planetary landmass and soil with predominance of wet quality. A wetland ecosystem is a terrestrial ecosystem usually inundated or saturated by surface or ground water frequented enough to support a specific type of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions. This exact definition is also referred to as 'wetland' or 'WETLAND'. Specific types of wetland ecosystems are also referred to as EstuarineWetland, LacustrineWetland, MarineWetland, PalustrineWetland, and TerrestialWetland. Additionally, it carries several other narrow synonyms that often describe different types of wetland ecosystems, such as RiparianWetland, back marsh, backswamp, backwater, barrier flat, blanket bog, bog, and cienaga among many others. Some related synonyms for the wetland ecosystem include moor, morass, and muskeg."

In terms of definition, a Lagrangian point is a site where the combined gravitational pull of two large astronomical bodies allows a smaller body, affected only by gravity, to maintain a stable position relative to these large bodies and orbit with them due to the centripetal force.
Additionally, the term ""Lagrangian point"" is also known by several exact synonyms including L-points, Lagrange points, and libration points."

column1: @prefix : <https://zaitoun.dev/onto/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:woodland_ecosystem rdfs:label ""woodland ecosystem""
rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction
owl:onProperty :has_part
owl:someValuesFrom :woodland_canopy ],
:terrestrial_ecosystem

:has_definition ""An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities are spaced sufficiently far apart to allow sunlight to illuminate the understory."" .
:has_part rdfs:label ""has part"" .
:terrestrial_ecosystem rdfs:label ""terrestrial ecosystem"" .
:woodland_canopy rdfs:label ""woodland canopy"" .

,The woodland ecosystem is a subclass of the terrestrial ecosystem and it includes certain elements from the woodland canopy. It is defined as an ecosystem that is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form. In this ecosystem, members of these communities are spaced sufficiently far apart to allow sunlight to illuminate the understory."
